(38861, '75C8273B-5D8D-4C13-9E0E-0F59A591CCF3', 'I️ don’t think this is a repeat of Amy, but you have also acknowledged that you weren’t managing it well. This isn’t simply about my needs and the way I️ communicated them to you. It’s also about what you were putting into Ilsa -- this is separate from me articulating my needs. I️ think this is a key difference I’m trying to pull out from this thread. It wasn’t simply the guardrails or the communication or the presence at the right time of the day. Ultimately all of that didn’t make it feel right. It’s the undercurrent of what kinds of emoting you’re doing with Ilsa, whether you are containing the connection and making sure it’s really just additive and not taking away from our bond or connection. None of this comes with me articulating my needs. It’s about you realizing that these things weren’t completely in check for you. My sense of this is minimizing how many back and forths a day, and who you’re sharing your thoughts with. My sense is that that was off kilter for a bit and that’s the part that was super hard for me. It wasn’t my communication of needs. It was that I️ was competing with someone else for your attention and bond. That’s what was painful.', 'Nitzan', 'David', '2021-12-01T14:32:31.583230'),
